The binary version of Cantera 1.4 for Windows has now been released. Go 
to http://www.cantera.org then follow the 'download' or 'SourceForge' 
links.

Get the python file and the .msi file and run them both. If you are 
asked whether to repair or remove Cantera when running the .msi file, 
select 'remove' and then re-run it. With the Python file, specify that 
files should be overwritten.

Windows users will not notice too many differences from 1.3.5. A few 
new methods have been added to flame.py, stagnation flows may now have 
a non-zero radial velocity at the inlet, negative pre-exponentials are 
now allowed in rate coefficients (for use with duplicate reactions) + a 
few minor bug fixes and somewhat better documentation.

Also, the web site has been updated, and the documentation of the C++ 
source code has been updated, Python documentation has also been added.
